{"name":"Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Sites.Closed","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Sites.SheafOfTypes","Mathlib.Order.Closure"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L320-L325","name":"CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator_close","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator_close","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L314-L317","name":"CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator_self","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator_self","doc":"The topology given by the closure operator `J.close` on a Grothendieck topology is the same as `J`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L294-L308","name":"CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator","doc":"A closure (increasing, inflationary and idempotent) operation on sieves that commutes with pullback\ninduces a Grothendieck topology.\nIn fact, such operations are in bijection with Grothendieck topologies.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L293-L293","name":"CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator_sieves","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.topologyOfClosureOperator_sieves","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L272-L285","name":"CategoryTheory.topology_eq_iff_same_sheaves","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.topology_eq_iff_same_sheaves","doc":"If being a sheaf for `J₁` is equivalent to being a sheaf for `J₂`, then `J₁ = J₂`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L251-L268","name":"CategoryTheory.le_topology_of_closedSieves_isSheaf","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.le_topology_of_closedSieves_isSheaf","doc":"If presheaf of `J₁`-closed sieves is a `J₂`-sheaf then `J₁ ≤ J₂`. Note the converse is true by\n`classifier_isSheaf` and `isSheaf_of_le`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L197-L245","name":"CategoryTheory.classifier_isSheaf","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.classifier_isSheaf","doc":"The presheaf of `J`-closed sieves is a `J`-sheaf.\nThe proof of this is adapted from [MM92], Chapter III, Section 7, Lemma 1.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L189-L191","name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.closedSieves","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.closedSieves","doc":"The presheaf sending each object to the set of `J`-closed sieves on it. This presheaf is a `J`-sheaf\n(and will turn out to be a subobject classifier for the category of `J`-sheaves).\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L188-L188","name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.closedSieves_map_coe","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.closedSieves_map_coe","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L188-L188","name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.closedSieves_obj","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.closedSieves_obj","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L177-L179","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.closed_iff_closed","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.closed_iff_closed","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L170-L173","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.closureOperator","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.closureOperator","doc":"A Grothendieck topology induces a natural family of closure operators on sieves. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L169-L169","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.closureOperator_apply_apply","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.closureOperator_apply_apply","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L155-L165","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_eq_top_iff_mem","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_eq_top_iff_mem","doc":"The sieve `S` is in the topology iff its closure is the maximal sieve. This shows that the closure\noperator determines the topology.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L146-L148","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_close","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_close","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L141-L142","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.monotone_close","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.monotone_close","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L129-L137","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.pullback_close","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.pullback_close","doc":"Closing under `J` is stable under pullback. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L124-L125","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_eq_self_of_isClosed","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_eq_self_of_isClosed","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L111-L121","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.isClosed_iff_close_eq_self","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.isClosed_iff_close_eq_self","doc":"The sieve `S` is closed iff its closure is equal to itself. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L106-L107","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_isClosed","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_isClosed","doc":"The closure of a sieve is closed. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L100-L102","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.le_close_of_isClosed","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.le_close_of_isClosed","doc":"The closure of a sieve `S` is the largest closed sieve which contains `S` (justifying the name\n\"closure\").\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L92-L94","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.isClosed_pullback","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.isClosed_pullback","doc":"Being `J`-closed is stable under pullback. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L86-L88","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.covers_iff_mem_of_isClosed","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.covers_iff_mem_of_isClosed","doc":"If `S` is `J₁`-closed, then `S` covers exactly the arrows it contains. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L81-L82","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.IsClosed","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.IsClosed","doc":"A sieve is closed for the Grothendieck topology if it contains every arrow it covers.\nIn the case of the usual topology on a topological space, this means that the open cover contains\nevery open set which it covers.\n\nNote this has no relation to a closed subset of a topological space.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L71-L72","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.le_close","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.le_close","doc":"Any sieve is smaller than its closure. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L65-L67","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close","doc":"The `J`-closure of a sieve is the collection of arrows which it covers. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.lean#L64-L64","name":"CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_apply","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Closed.html#CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.close_apply","doc":""}]}